==English==

===Etymology===
From the {{D.}} composite word '''Rugzak''', made up from the nouns [[rug]] ([[back]]) and [[zak]] ([[bag]])

===Noun===
'''rucksack''' (''plural'' [[rucksacks]])
# a [[bag]] carried on the [[back]] or [[shoulder]], supported by [[strap]]s

====Synonyms====
* [[back pack]] or [[backpack]]
* [[knapsack]]
* [[haversack]]

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[rugzak]] ''m''

